## 3. Core Logic Flow: Resume Upload → Career Roadmap

The end-to-end user journey from uploading a resume to receiving a personalized career roadmap involves **8 distinct steps** across frontend and backend:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["👤 User uploads PDF<br/><b>frontend/app/resume/page.tsx</b>"] --> B["📤 POST /api/resume/upload<br/><b>backend/routers/resume.py</b>"]
    B --> C["📄 extract_text_from_pdf()<br/><b>PyMuPDF (fitz)</b>"]
    C --> D["💾 Save resume_text to Supabase<br/><b>profiles table</b>"]
    D --> E["🔬 POST /api/analysis/start<br/><b>backend/routers/analysis.py</b>"]
    E --> F["🐙 github_service.get_full_github_data()<br/>🟡 leetcode_service.get_full_leetcode_data()"]
    F --> G["🧠 gemini_service.run_combined_analysis()<br/><b>Single Gemini 2.5 Flash API call</b>"]
    G --> H["💾 Save to Supabase<br/><b>analyses table</b>"]
    H --> I["📊 Render on /analysis page<br/><b>frontend/app/analysis/page.tsx</b>"]
```

### Step-by-Step Breakdown

| Step | Location | Function / Component | Description |
|------|----------|---------------------|-------------|
| **1. Upload** | [resume/page.tsx](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/frontend/app/resume/page.tsx) | `handleUpload()` | Validates PDF (type + 5MB limit), sends as `FormData` to backend |
| **2. Parse PDF** | [routers/resume.py](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/resume.py#L31-L91) | `upload_resume()` → `extract_text_from_pdf()` | PyMuPDF extracts text from all pages |
| **3. Persist** | [routers/resume.py:80](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/resume.py#L80) | `supabase.table("profiles").update()` | Stores `resume_text` and `resume_filename` in user's profile row |
| **4. Trigger Analysis** | [analysis/page.tsx](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/frontend/app/analysis/page.tsx#L132-L189) | `runAnalysis()` | Frontend POSTs to `/api/analysis/start` with `user_id` |
| **5. Fetch External Data** | [routers/analysis.py:76-83](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/analysis.py#L76-L83) | `github_service.get_full_github_data()` + `leetcode_service.get_full_leetcode_data()` | Parallel async calls to GitHub REST API + LeetCode GraphQL API |
| **6. AI Analysis** | [gemini_service.py:55-173](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/services/gemini_service.py#L55-L173) | `_run_combined_analysis()` | **Single Gemini API call** combining all data into one structured prompt. Returns JSON with: `analysis`, `career_paths`, `skill_gaps`, `roadmap` |
| **7. Cache & Persist** | [gemini_service.py:176-199](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/services/gemini_service.py#L176-L199) + [analysis.py:114-135](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/analysis.py#L114-L135) | `_get_cached_analysis()` + Supabase upsert | In-memory cache for session deduplication. Results saved to `analyses` table |
| **8. Render** | [analysis/page.tsx:259-418](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/frontend/app/analysis/page.tsx#L259-L418) | React components | Displays: Experience Level badge, Strengths chips, Career Paths cards (with match %), Skill Gaps table (have/need), and week-by-week Roadmap timeline |

### Key Architecture Details

- **Single AI Call Pattern**: The `gemini_service` consolidates what were originally 6 separate API calls (analyze, career paths, skill gaps, roadmap, etc.) into **1 combined prompt** that returns a single structured JSON. Individual functions (`analyze_profile`, `generate_career_paths`, `generate_skill_gaps`, `generate_roadmap`) all read from the same cached result.

- **In-Memory Cache**: `_analysis_cache` dictionary keyed on `str(github_data) + str(leetcode_data) + str(resume_text[:100])`. This means the same analysis is not re-run within a server session.

- **Flexible Field Parsing**: The frontend `analysis/page.tsx` handles multiple possible field names from the AI (e.g., `name`/`career_name`/`title` for career paths) due to non-deterministic Gemini JSON output.

