### 4.2 — TODO Comments

| File | Line | TODO |
|------|------|------|
| [profile.py](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/profile.py#L24) | 24 | `user_id = "temp_user_id"  # TODO: Extract from auth token` |

> [!WARNING]
> The `profile.py` router (the **basic** one) hardcodes `user_id = "temp_user_id"` instead of extracting it from the auth token. This is a **security gap** — the `profile_enhanced.py` router correctly uses Supabase-provided `user_id`, but this older file does not. Both are mounted on `/api/profile`.

---

### 4.3 — Known Bugs & Architectural Concerns

| Severity | Issue | Location | Details |
|----------|-------|----------|---------|
| 🔴 **High** | Hardcoded `user_id` | [profile.py:24](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/profile.py#L24) | `"temp_user_id"` is used instead of real auth token extraction |
| 🔴 **High** | Duplicate route prefix collision | [main.py:39,43](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/main.py#L39-L43) | Both `profile.py` and `profile_enhanced.py` are mounted on `/api/profile` — potential route conflicts |
| 🟡 **Medium** | Interview router uses `request.user_id` instead of `body.user_id` | [interview.py:57,65](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/interview.py#L57-L65) | `generate_questions()` accesses `request.user_id` (the HTTP Request object) instead of `body.user_id` (the Pydantic model). This will crash at runtime with `AttributeError` |
| 🟡 **Medium** | Jobs endpoint returns only **mock data** | [jobs.py:20-48](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/routers/jobs.py#L20-L48) | `GET /api/jobs` is hardcoded mock jobs. Real SerpAPI integration exists in `jobs_service.py` but isn't wired into the main endpoint |
| 🟡 **Medium** | `generate_skill_gaps()` drops `leetcode_data` | [gemini_service.py:257](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/services/gemini_service.py#L257) | Passes `leetcode_data={}` to `_get_cached_analysis()`, so if skill gaps are requested independently, it generates a cache miss and makes a new (incomplete) API call |
| 🟡 **Medium** | `generate_roadmap()` drops both `github_data` and `leetcode_data` | [gemini_service.py:271-274](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/services/gemini_service.py#L271-L274) | Passes `github_data={}, leetcode_data={}` — same cache-miss issue as above |
| 🟢 **Low** | In-memory cache not bounded | [gemini_service.py:21](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/backend/services/gemini_service.py#L21) | `_analysis_cache = {}` grows indefinitely, no TTL or LRU eviction |
| 🟢 **Low** | Next.js middleware is a no-op | [middleware.ts](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/frontend/middleware.ts) | `middleware.ts` simply calls `NextResponse.next()` — no auth protection at the middleware level. Auth checks are done per-page instead |
| 🟢 **Low** | `lib/api.ts` not used by pages | [api.ts](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/frontend/lib/api.ts) | Pages make direct `fetch()` calls instead of using the typed `api` client. The `api.ts` module appears to be unused dead code |
| 🟢 **Low** | Outdated README | [README.md:19](file:///c:/project-2026/Career-navigator/README.md#L19) | References Claude API, Anthropic key, and missing env vars for Gemini |

